View a node in the codebase tree (directory, file, or symbol)

Usage: moss view [OPTIONS] [TARGET]

Arguments:
  [TARGET]  Target: path, path/Symbol, Parent/method, file:line, or SymbolName

Options:
  -r, --root <ROOT>        Root directory (defaults to current directory)
  -d, --depth <DEPTH>      Depth of expansion (0=names only, 1=signatures, 2=with children, -1=all)
  -n, --line-numbers       Show line numbers
      --deps               Show dependencies (imports/exports)
  -k, --kind <KIND>        Filter by symbol kind: class, function, method
      --types-only         Show only type definitions (class, struct, enum, interface, type alias)
      --tests              Include test functions and test modules (hidden by default)
      --raw                Disable smart display (no collapsing single-child dirs)
      --focus[=<MODULE>]   Focus view: show target at high detail, imports at signature level
      --resolve-imports    Resolve imports: inline signatures of specific imported symbols
      --full               Show full source code
      --docs               Show full docstrings
      --no-parent          Hide parent/ancestor context (shown by default for nested symbols)
      --context            Context view: skeleton + imports combined
      --dir-context        Prepend directory context (.context.md files from hierarchy)
      --exclude <PATTERN>  Exclude paths matching pattern or @alias
      --only <PATTERN>     Include only paths matching pattern or @alias
  -i, --case-insensitive   Case-insensitive symbol matching
      --history [<N>]      Show git history for symbol (last N changes)
      --json               Output as JSON
      --jq <EXPR>          Filter JSON output with jq expression (implies --json)
      --pretty             Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact            Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
  -h, --help               Print help
